		<title>How to enable Mono Audio in Samsung Galaxy S5(4.4.2)</title>
		<link>https://www.sprogroup.com/how-to-enable-mono-audio-in-samsung-galaxy-s54-4-2.html</link>
					<comments>https://www.sprogroup.com/how-to-enable-mono-audio-in-samsung-galaxy-s54-4-2.html#respond</comments>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Michael Vu]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Sat, 03 Jan 2015 08:17:59 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Experience]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Accessibility]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Galaxy S5]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Hearing]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Mono audio]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://sprogroup.com/?p=223</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Mono audio is a feature in Samsung Galaxy S5 that allows us to switch sound output from stereo to mono. This is very useful for us when we use earphones or we have problem with our ear that make you can only hear well with 1 side (left or right ear). Now, let me show [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Mono audio is a feature in Samsung Galaxy S5 that allows us to switch sound output from stereo to mono. This is very useful for us when we use earphones or we have problem with our ear that make you can only hear well with 1 side (left or right ear). Now, let me show you how to enable this feature:</p>
<p><a href="http://sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screenshot_2014-12-27-03-48-28-e1419655538641.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-138" src="http://sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screenshot_2014-12-27-03-48-28-168x300.png" alt="Screenshot_2014-12-27-03-48-28" width="168" height="300" /></a>   <a href="http://sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screenshot_2014-12-27-03-48-20-e1419655689358.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-139" src="http://sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screenshot_2014-12-27-03-48-20-168x300.png" alt="Screenshot_2014-12-27-03-48-20" width="168" height="300" /></a>   <a href="http://sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-15-05-25.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-222" src="http://sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-15-05-25-168x300.png" alt="Screenshot_2015-01-03-15-05-25" width="168" height="300" srcset="https://www.sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-15-05-25-168x300.png 168w, https://www.sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-15-05-25-576x1024.png 576w, https://www.sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-15-05-25.png 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 168px) 100vw, 168px" /></a></p>
<p>How to use:</p>
<ol>
<li>Swipe down the top of screen to open the <strong>notification panel</strong> and then tap to <strong>setting</strong> icon</li>
<li>From the setting function, select <strong>Device</strong> Tag and scroll down to <strong>Personalization</strong> section and then tap to <strong>Accessibility</strong>.</li>
<li>Tap to <strong>Hearing</strong>.</li>
<li>Select the check box at <strong>Mono audio</strong> feature to enable this feature.</li>
<li>From these steps, the <strong>Mono audio</strong> has been enabled.</li>
</ol>
]]></content:encoded>
					
