		<title>How to modify/change screen color from Negative to normal color in Samsung Galaxy S5 (4.4.2)</title>
		<link>https://www.sprogroup.com/how-to-modifychange-screen-color-from-negative-to-normal-color-in-samsung-galaxy-s5-4-4-2.html</link>
					<comments>https://www.sprogroup.com/how-to-modifychange-screen-color-from-negative-to-normal-color-in-samsung-galaxy-s5-4-4-2.html#respond</comments>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Michael Vu]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Sat, 03 Jan 2015 04:20:57 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Experience]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Accessibility]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Galaxy S5]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Negative Colors]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Vision]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://sprogroup.com/?p=211</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[Sometime, because of some setting, your screen color looks like a negative color, it might happen when you turn on the negative colors feature which will inverse the screen display to the negative color. How to fix this issue and get back the normal screen color? It is very easy if you disable this feature [&#8230;]]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Sometime, because of some setting, your screen color looks like a negative color, it might happen when you turn on the negative colors feature which will inverse the screen display to the negative color. How to fix this issue and get back the normal screen color? It is very easy if you disable this feature in your phone.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="http://sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-04-03-46.png">    </a><a href="http://sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-04-03-46.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-139" src="http://sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screenshot_2014-12-27-03-48-20-168x300.png" alt="Screenshot_2014-12-27-03-48-20" width="200" height="355" /></a>    <a href="http://sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-04-03-46.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-213" src="http://sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-04-03-46-168x300.png" alt="Screenshot_2015-01-03-04-03-46" width="200" height="356" srcset="https://www.sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-04-03-46-168x300.png 168w, https://www.sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-04-03-46-300x533.png 300w, https://www.sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-04-03-46-576x1024.png 576w, https://www.sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-04-03-46.png 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></a>    <a href="http://sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-04-03-46.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-138" src="http://sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/Screenshot_2014-12-27-03-48-28-168x300.png" alt="Screenshot_2014-12-27-03-48-28" width="200" height="355" /></a>   <a href="http://sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-04-07-42.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-214" src="http://sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-04-07-42-168x300.png" alt="Screenshot_2015-01-03-04-07-42" width="200" height="356" srcset="https://www.sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-04-07-42-168x300.png 168w, https://www.sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-04-07-42-300x533.png 300w, https://www.sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-04-07-42-576x1024.png 576w, https://www.sprogroup.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/Screenshot_2015-01-03-04-07-42.png 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>How to use:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Swipe down the top of the screen to open the <strong>Notification Panel</strong></li>
<li>Tap to <strong>Setting</strong> Icon</li>
<li>Move to <strong>Device</strong> Tag and select <strong>Accessibility</strong></li>
<li>Tap to <strong>Vision</strong></li>
<li>Move to the <strong>Negative Colors</strong> feature and clear the check box.</li>
<li>Observe: The screen color will be reversed back to the normal.</li>
</ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
